<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-62-1133 </DOCNO><TEXT>A rotary anode for an X-ray tube is described comprising a disc and ablackening coating on at least a part of a surface of the disc. The blackeningcoating comprises a sintered porous composition of titanium grains havingan essentially dendritic structure of a size from 0.5 to 150 {mu}m, anda least one high melting point melting having a melting point greaterthan 2500{sup 0}C the amount of the high melting point metal in the coatingbeing between about 5 and 60% by weight.</TEXT></DOC>